reviews.review: To see star wars as a jaded quasi-film critic, channeling your political or social frustrations into a fantasy movie, is a tragic mistake. Star Wars has always been about escape, and joy, and this movie delivers.
Not as good as I hoped but not as terrible as some reviewers have said!

Everything was random. I think a lot must have been lost in editing. I'm not going to bash this but it honestly just made me sad. Sad that the greatest story to me in my lifetime ended this way. Just sad about it

Not good at all!  I was so hoping to see something that brought the trilogy together.  But it was a mixed up no sense plot that hurts the other two movies!  There is no emotion in this movie.  I should have felt something but nothing.  Waste of great new and old characters!!  Only good thing about it is the score and special effects are really good in spots.  Other than that the plot is mind numbing.  Don't wast your money.  I'm so sad about this.
Darth sidious was the best part of the film. Killing Leia was disrespectful. I have many negative thoughts about the movie that I'm going to just keep to myself due to the evil fandom.  1ROTJ 2 TPM
It was really good overall. I would watch it again. I think the story did justice to a lot of different characters, new and old alike.
Ties up the loose ends nicely!

The final film of the Star Wars saga concludes with some timing issues and what felt like an overall rushed job. The film is busy. It has a lot going on. Too many new characters, new planets in a fast-paced mind-screw of action and story plot, the film should be more adequately called the "Rise of Palpatine".

Where was Anakin Skywalker?
Or Luke even?
The Knights of Who?
 
Just poor pacing in a rushed job to get done and at the same time try to 
fix the mess of Ryan Johnson's crap story TLJ. It's hard JJ I get it.

I'm 48 years old and this story arch has been apart of my life since I was 5 years old. Disney could and should have done a better job for fans. Don't get me wrong there are positives, like great light saber duels and space battles that are awesome effects shots, but the films pace and story plot are choppy at best.

I left the theater feeling like my head had just been dragged through the spice-mines of Kessel and then crushed in a garbage compactor.  

Great concern I have with the future of the franchise from a Galaxy far far away . . . 

- Russell
Rockstar Magazine
